# QA API Pilot scaffold .gitignore
#
# What gets pushed to git is the scaffold ONLY (the agents, docs, templates, example env).
# Anything created locally by running an agent is gitignored - new users get their own
# project-specific copies when they run /qa-api-test-setup.

# ----- Secrets and project-specific config -----

.env

# ----- Generated by /qa-api-test-setup -----

# Helper scripts written from templates (per-project values inside).
# Anchored to repo root so the .claude/templates/ sources stay tracked.
/run-tests.sh
/generate-issues.py

# Newman environment file (auto-generated from the collection)
newman-env.json

# ----- Generated by Postman / agent runs -----

# Main project collection export (re-generated by /qa-api-test-setup and refreshed by /qa-api-sync)
*-collection.json

# Spec drift snapshot (auto-renamed daily by /qa-api-sync)
api-snapshot-*.json

# ----- Generated by Newman + generate-issues.py runs -----

newman-reports/
collection-run-issues/

# ----- OpenAPI spec, if you store it locally rather than fetching from a URL -----

# Uncomment one of these if your spec lives in the repo and is part of the scaffold,
# OR leave them gitignored if the spec is project-specific data.
# api-docs*.json
# openapi*.json
# openapi*.yaml

# ----- IDE / OS -----

.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# ----- Claude Code per-project settings (already in .claude/) -----

.claude/settings.local.json

# ----- Optional: local memory / scratch files -----

flow-analysis.md
*.scratch.md
